----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Software and Hardware requirements.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	i) This extension requires LexEVS release 5.0 or above.
	
 	ii) Development system are required to install the Sun Java Development Kit (SDK) or Java Runtime Environment (JRE)
 		version 1.5.0_11 or above.
 		
 	iii) Maven 2.1 or greater.
 	
 	iiii) For software and hardware dependencies for the system hosting the LexEVS runtime, refer to https://cabig-kc.nci.nih.gov/Vocab/KC/index.php/LexEVS_5.0_Documentation.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Instructions to build Persistence Layer
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	i) To build artifacts 

		- mvn clean package
		
	ii) Other Maven build goals can be executed as necessary, such as building source, creating javadocs, etc.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Instructions to generate LexEVS Hibernate Java Beans and Mappings.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	  
	i) Hibernate Generated Beans and Mapping files are included - but can be regenerated at any time.
		
		- Edit the Hibernate Generation Configuration file
			- in /src/main/config/generation, edit the file 'hibernate.cfg.xml'. The database configuration given must
			  contain a LexEVS 5.0 table set (populated or not).
			- Make sure the database that is pointed to does NOT contain table prefixes (i.e. it was loaded in Single Database Mode).
		
		- Execute the Maven command "mvn hibernate3:hbm2hbmxml hibernate3:hbm2java"
		
		- Java Beans will be place in the /src/main/java/org/LexGrid/persistence/model package
		
		- Hibernate mapping files will be placed in /src/main/resources/mapping.
	
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Instructions to test Persistence Layer.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	i) To run the automated tests, use the command 'mvn test'.
		- Test results will be located in the '/target' directory.